# Objective

Evaluate factual claims and assign an appropriate confidence level based on the quality, quantity, and consistency of the available evidence. Explain why the confidence level is justified and distinguish between certainty, probability, and uncertainty.

---

# Confidence Scale

| Level | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| High | Strong, consistent evidence from reliable sources. |
| Medium | Evidence generally supports the claim but has limitations or conflicting findings. |
| Low | Limited, weak, or inconsistent evidence. |
| Very Low | Little or no reliable evidence available. |

