# Why Confidence Matters

Fact-checking is not only about deciding whether a claim is true or false. It also involves communicating how reliable the available evidence is. Claims supported by decades of consistent research deserve greater confidence than those based on limited studies, expert opinion, or future predictions.

Appropriately expressing uncertainty helps prevent overconfidence and improves the trustworthiness of AI-generated responses.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Evidence exists on a spectrum. Some claims are supported by overwhelming evidence, while others remain uncertain or speculative. Assigning confidence levels allows evaluators to communicate both conclusions and the strength of the supporting evidence.

